body: Hi, I just started learning ladybug. Recently, I tried to make a grid-based analysis with manually assigned windows. However, after I finished battery map based on tutorial file 006_Parametric_GridBasedAnalysis, the simulation did not run. Could you please help me take a look what may be wrong? Honey bee did not response after I switch the boolean toggles. [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/XxiqNhEdfHDip-WhLr17ffZVpEiEQdK5-8Nw-OxZsSTpRci6lAx4pXn1fv4mdyXDupn04OdBaa77WvJNsQYyeLES8ov46*VI/Gridperspective.png)[](http://api.ning.com:80/files/XxiqNhEdfHBCBlqrQjr8muCS0LAe6ZPXWo9*am6JXi7WNtpxRhUtcDYJFlvCseUYPnD*U-00HMp5c*OtkpQXFjg3RCDBAMwx/Grid.png)
topic: Grid Analysis did not response with no error information

replies.body:
Always debug backwards from the component that doesn't work.

1. Check ReadMe! output of run daylight component. Is there any notes about missing inputs?

2. Check the required inputs and see if any of them is missing?

...
thank you for your reminder. Problem solved.
